We recommended to:

a.	Instruct the Municipal Accountant to effect the necessary adjustments on the omissions/errors to correct the reported balances of the affected accounts in the Financial Statements;

b.	Prepare a reconciliation statement for the discrepancies noted in the balances of Due to other NGAs account vis-a-vis NGAs records and effect the necessary adjusting entries, if any and coordinate or make representation to NGAs Accountant to settle the variance.;

c.	Observe the additional information required by PPSAS that is not shown on the face of the financial statements but relevant to an understanding.

We recommended the following:

a. to require the Municipal Accountant for an issuance of an Order of payment to AOs for any outstanding cash advance a day after its liquidation has been due and enforce full refund of any unexpended cash advance.

b. Stop granting additional cash advances to those officials or employees with un-liquidated cash advances;

c. Strictly enforce the liquidation of cash advances within the prescribed period as provided in COA Circular No. 97-002;

d. Withhold the salary of the Accountable Officers who are still employed in the municipality who failed to liquidate their outstanding cash advances until the full amount is settled/liquidated

We recommended the following:

a) to ensure that projects to be charged to the 20% Development Fund should have the nature of investment or capital expenditures such as concreting of roads etc. that would improve the socio-economic condition and environmental management in the delivery of services for the betterment of the constituents;

b) Properly appropriate in the General Fund Proper expenses for the maintenance of streetlights, pesticides and seedlings and exclude the above program’s expenses in the 20% Development Fund; and to exercise prudence in the utilization of the 20% Development Fund as provided by the Local Government Code and Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2011-01.

We recommended the following:

a) to require the Philippine Councilor Leagues (PCL) and all other leagues organized by elective officials, to issue a Government Official Receipts (OR)/Accountable Form No. 51 (AF 51)), for all collections made so that proper financial accountability could be established;

b) Ensure that all future registration fee payments for PCL conducted trainings/seminars/activities be receipted with a Government Official Receipt which is AF No. 51, to avoid audit suspension and/or disallowance.
